how do you live with constant pain from rheumatoid arthritis i hurt all of the time some times i just wish that i can lay down and die i don't want to be so druged that my mind is fussy any pointers i have rheumatoid arthritis and i know how bad the pain can be at times i know what you mean about not wanting the fuzzy head i had to take a diclofenac tab the other day i made the mistake of driving a few blocks and i almost fell to sleep driving you can try a relaxing soak in the tub i do that sometimes sometimes i think if i got down into the tub i wouldn't be able to get out again but the soak does help my dr has me on methotrexate once weekly to try to stop the decease from progressing some cities have support groups for sufferers if you ever need to talk to others who are going through the same try asking your dr about a support group Rheumatoid arthritis COX-2 inhibitor Psoriasis Osteoarthritis Arthritis Methotrexate Diclofenac Psoriatic arthritis Folic acid Rheumatism Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug Immunosuppressive drug Sulfasalazine Celecoxib Carpal tunnel syndrome Tuberculosis Equine conformation Textile manufacturing Lupus erythematosus Have I Got News For You Cindy Sheehan Hot tub The Catcher in the Rye Childbirth Pain Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Sj__gren's syndrome Billy Bowden Orthopedic surgery Ankylosing spondylitis Crohn's disease Theory of conduct Social rule Shaggy dog story One Tree Hill (TV series) Sandy Koufax Ibuprofen Paget's disease of bone Euthanasia Bon Jovi Conjunctivitis The Shining (film) Jackass: The Movie The Amber Spyglass Humanist Movement Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Pointer Fight Club True Crime: Streets of LA Breastfeeding Something Awful Sami Brady The Pet Sounds Sessions Jon Secada Piccolo Junior Saga The Amazing Race Out-of-body experience Rofecoxib Aerial (dance move) Autoimmune diseases Methylsulfonylmethane Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Menstrual cup Downing Street memo Tai Chi Chuan Xbox 360 Temporal arteritis Timon